  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ensuring the Support for the Rohingya Refugees Affected by the Fire in March 2021</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On 22 March 2021, a massive fire broke out in the Camps 9, 8E and 8W housing Rohingya refugees in the Cox&#x2019;s Bazar District, Bangladesh. All of these camps are in IOM&#x2019;s Site Management Area of Responsibility (AOR). The fire consumed the shelters and all personal belongings of thousands of Rohingya refugee families and essential facilities in the camps. With the key objective of ensuring the continuity of life-saving services for the Rohingya refugees affected by the fire, IOM is focusing and upscaling efforts on shelter/non-food items, water, sanitation and hygiene, health, site management and site development, and protection.</narrative>
  </description>
